{"TopicId":142446,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"The jet engine contrails look disgusting at lower altitudes.","CreatedByName":"Columbia","CreatedById":135031,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T03:08:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Columbia","CreatedById":135031,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T03:08:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey look good when you\u0027re at high altitude, not so much when taking off or landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI get that you need something to indicate whether or not the engines are throttling up, and it might work for, say, RAPIERS and ramjets, but on the Wheesley and Juno?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gpZyTW5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gpZyTW5.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mTO6Key.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mTO6Key.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JcDoYxq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JcDoYxq.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. Eugh. no.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn alternative:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know the exhaust at the other end of an airliner\u0027s engine? It\u0027s sort of a blur?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022?url=%2Fcmsmedia%2F85%2Fe8%2F54a99d85410\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.usnews.com/dims4/USNEWS/cdd2df7/2147483647/thumbnail/652x435%3E/quality/85/?url=%2Fcmsmedia%2F85%2Fe8%2F54a99d85410f8364a4cb8080c727%2Fresizes%2F1500%2F160208-airplane-editorial.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat might work, but less intense.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt high altitude, say, 5000m, the contrails could be displayed:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Contrail_fourengined_airplane.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.aviationexplorer.com/Contrail_fourengined_airplane.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n..That\u0027s it. Tell me what you think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-25T05:48:31Z\u0022 title=\u002206/25/2016 05:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Columbia\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wyzard","CreatedById":162363,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T04:12:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sort of blur effect is more complex and GPU-intensive than puffs of smoke, so it\u0027s more likely to cause a framerate hit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the bigger issue is that at high \u003Cem\u003Espeed\u003C/em\u003E, the contrail looks like a bunch of isolated dots instead of a continuous trail.\u00A0 It\u0027d be better if they were connected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rdivine","CreatedById":66317,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T04:15:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222646388\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022142446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466827969\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162363\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wyzard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Wyzard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sort of blur effect is more complex and GPU-intensive than puffs of smoke, so it\u0027s more likely to cause a framerate hit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the bigger issue is that at high \u003Cem\u003Espeed\u003C/em\u003E, the contrail looks like a bunch of isolated dots instead of a continuous trail.\u00A0 It\u0027d be better if they were connected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a simple way is to \u0022stretch\u0022 the particles in the prograde direction so it looks sort of connected, without making new particles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wyzard","CreatedById":162363,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T05:43:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027d probably work better to just replace the particles with a strip of quadrilaterals, like a smoke-textured banner trailing behind the engine.\u00A0 (Naturally, the texture would have to be animated sliding backward along the strip at the speed that the engine is moving forward.)\u00A0 The same strip could also be used for the heat-ripple shader effect, if desired.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T17:55:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree and very much support this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI like how it worked in the old IL-2 game. The exhaust smoke was simply drawn as a line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yakuzi","CreatedById":85181,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T23:37:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002272433\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/72433-bahamutod/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@BahamutoD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has previously done some amazing work on\u00A0the exhaust refraction\u00A0you\u0027re suggesting:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/cLMY6poKtds?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBahamutoD mentioned there\u0027s no significant performance hit (apart from specific viewing angles). Would be great to see in the (stock) game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pincushionman","CreatedById":98495,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T23:41:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP isn\u0027t usually GPU-bound, so a graphics shader on a few engines shouldn\u0027t bottleneck anybody\u0027s game. Plus it\u0027s the kind of thing thst should be disableable-able\u2026able\u2026anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T00:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222648982\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022142446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466984511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298495\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pincushionman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, pincushionman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na few engines\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, except for that one guy who tries to cover the entire\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in a shower of heat refraction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-27T00:11:39Z\u0022 title=\u002206/27/2016 12:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by cubinator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T05:22:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222646342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022142446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466824131\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135031\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Columbia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/25/2016 at 5:08 AM, Columbia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt high altitude, say, 5000m, the contrails could be displayed:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou surely mean\u00A0Chemtrails, right?\u003Cbr\u003E\n...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T09:15:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222649295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022142446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467004950\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou surely mean\u00A0Chemtrails, right?\u003Cbr\u003E\n...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\